The paper deals with interactive proofs, which are a fundamental concept in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also introduces a mechanism-design approach to define a multi-prover interactive-proof model, which involves game theory and incentives (cs.GT). The paper discusses the strategic behavior of service providers in outsourcing applications, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The analysis of the resulting extensive-form game with imperfect information involves concepts from algorithmic game theory and decision theory, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
